        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 5:30PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 530 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Secaucus, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Jersey City, Hoboken, Secaucus, Ridgefield, Midtown Manhattan,
Harlem, Astoria, Lower East Side, Union City, East Village, SoHo,
Kearny, Fort Lee, Brooklyn Heights, and Long Island City.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
